<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 7:12PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of western Dallam and
northwestern Hartley Counties through 745 PM CDT...
At 712 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sedan, or 17 miles north of Amistad, moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Texline and Ware.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
